<section id="assumptions" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="assumptions">Assumptions</h3>
<p>This model assumes a “perfectly mixed” pool where every quarter in the metro area has an equal chance of landing in your pocket. In reality, quarters might cluster in local businesses or laundromats, potentially <strong>increasing</strong> the local probability even further!</p>
<p>What do you think? Does this make you want to start marking your quarters?</p>


